        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 4:03PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 403 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Bremen, or 7 miles northwest of Shawnee, moving
northwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Lexington, Somerset, Shawnee, Junction City, New Straitsville,
and Glenford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Charleston West Virginia.</instruction>
